terraform fmt
    * Fmt the scripts in canonical style
terraform plan
    * Plan for the execution
terraform apply
    * Apply the given plan
terraform console
    * Access the stuff present on the state file only
terraform state 
    * For state mangement
    * rm - to remove a particular resource from the state file
terraform import
    * Import resources into terraform
    * Need to manually define the configuration of the resource before we destroy it
terraform refresh
    * basically it does terraform apply --refresh-only --auto-approve. Risky
    * Instead use terraform apply --refresh-onl only to review the changes  